context: May wynne of me moo fees thus
To have moo floures swiche seven
Now good sires what wol ye bet than wel
In which ther were moo ymages
And with perre moo pynacles
And moo loves newe begonne
And moo loves casuelly
Mo discordes moo jelousies
Mo discordes moo jelousies
Mo murmures and moo novelries
Mo murmures and moo novelries
And moo dissymulacions
And moo berdys in two houres
And also moo renovelaunces
Mo lovedayes and acordes
Good werkes shal yow noght availle
Han these sory creatures
Where thou maist most tidynges here
What ladyes fairest been or best daunsynge
Of scoletermes Wyser men than thow
Withouten wordes mo they goon to bedde
This kyng of kynges proud was and elaat
His nayles whitter than the lylye flour
There been mo sterres God wot than a payre
And deyntees mo than been in my knowyng
A thousand sikes hotter than the gleede
I trowe he hadde wyves mo than oon
And ech of hem hadde wyves mo than two
For I shal telle ensamples mo than ten
He knew of hem mo legendes and lyves
And therwithal he knew of mo proverbes
